Package org.csdgn.amf3

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Externalizable
    Defines custom data capable of being stored in the Action Message Format (AMF).
    ExternalizableFactory
    Defines a factory for creating Externalizables.
    Trait
    This defines a Trait.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AmfArray
    Associated with the AMF true and false types.
    AmfBoolean
    Associated with the AMF true and false types.
    AmfByteArray
    This class handles byte buffer objects associated in the AMF.
    AmfDate
    This class handles date objects associated in the AMF.
    AmfDictionary
    Associated with the AMF dictionary type.
    AmfDouble
    Associated with the AMF double type.
    AmfFile
    Defines an AmfFile better known as a SOL (Shared Object Local) file.
    AmfInteger
    Associated with the AMF integer type.
    AmfIO
    This is an IO class to handle reading and writing from .SOL files and singularly serialized AmfValues.
    AmfNull
    Associated with the AMF null type.
    AmfObject
    Associated with the AMF object type.
    AmfPrimitive<T>
    Defines a single value that has a simple format.
    AmfString
    Associated with the AMF string type.
    AmfUndefined
    Associated with the AMF undefined type.
    AmfValue
    This class is the origin point for all Action Message Format (AMF) value types.
    AmfVector<E>
    Associated with the AMF undefined type.
    AmfVector.Double
    A specialized version of the AmfVector for Double values.
    AmfVector.Generic
    A version of the AmfVector for general values.
    AmfVector.Integer
    A specialized version of the AmfVector for Integer values.
    AmfVector.UnsignedInteger
    A specialized version of the AmfVector for Unsigned Integer values.
    AmfXml
    This class handles XML objects associated in the AMF.
    SimpleTrait
    A simple trait implementation that does not allow modification of its values.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    AmfType
    List of types associated with the the Amf Objects.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    UnexpectedDataException
    Thrown when an Externalizable or a AmfInputStream finds unexpected data during a read operation.
